            <p class="separator">Aims to provide a fast 2D player.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="row" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="100">

            <div class="col-md-6 col-lg-3">
              <div class="feature-block">
                <img src="assets/img/player/7985345.png" alt="img">
                <h4>Open Source</h4>
                <p>Next2D Player is available free of charge as open source software for personal and commercial use.</p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="col-md-6 col-lg-3">
              <div class="feature-block">
                <img src="assets/img/player/7504267.png" alt="img">
                <h4>Fast</h4>
                <p>Experience lightweight, fast, and beautiful anti-aliased rendering.</p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="col-md-6 col-lg-3">
              <div class="feature-block">
                <img src="assets/img/player/6323764.png" alt="img">
                <h4>Full WebGL support</h4>
                <p>emulation technology of "swf2js" is ported to realize Flash-like rendering of Filter, Shape, etc. in WebGL.</p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="col-md-6 col-lg-3">
              <div class="feature-block">
                <img src="assets/img/player/3666006.png" alt="img">
                <h4>Various Text Functions</h4>
                <p>Various text features such as fixed text, dynamic text input, and HTML text are included.</p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="col-md-6 col-lg-3">
              <div class="feature-block">
                <img src="assets/img/player/8267133.png" alt="img">
                <h4>Multi-Platform Support</h4>
                <p>Deliver interactive and visually appealing content from desktop to mobile with a single code base.</p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="col-md-6 col-lg-3">
              <div class="feature-block">
                <img src="assets/img/player/chrome.svg" alt="chrome">
